  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0db8 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dda\u0dc2\u0dca\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Give Prime Ministership to Dinesh",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna Gampaha District Member of Parliament Mr. Sisira Jayakodi has requested the Acting President to appoint Speaker of the House Dinesh Gunawardena as Acting Prime Minister.",
        "He also points out that this can be done according to the provisions of the constitution.",
        "After the office of President becomes vacant, the Prime Minister shall act in the office of President during the period between the appointment of a new President. He mentioned that since the post of Prime Minister will be vacant, the Acting President should appoint another cabinet minister according to the constitution to fill that position.",
        "He also states that this is stated in Article 40 (1) (c) of the Constitution.",
        "If the current Prime Minister is Acting President, according to the Constitution he must now appoint a Cabinet Minister for the post of Prime Minister. In 1993, Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe, who was then the leader of the House, became the Prime Minister. After the assassination of President Ranasinghe Premadasa, the then Prime Minister DB Wijetunga became the Acting President, and Mr. Wijetunga appointed Ranil Wickramasinghe, who was a member of the Cabinet at that time, as the Prime Minister. There, the tradition was to treat the Leader of the House of Parliament as senior and worthy after the Prime Minister. Accordingly, Mr. Jayakodi states that this time, Mr. Dinesh Gunawardena, who is the leader of the House and also a senior minister, should be appointed as the Acting Prime Minister."
      ],
